  "objectives": "Objective â€” Demonstrate required proficiency on navigation mission planning and navigation procedures.\r\nNote: Students preplan the missions in this block during academic classroom training. The simulator instructor should execute the profile to incorporate real world problems such as weather, alternate requirements, and approach restrictions.\r\nPractice departure and level off checks to include assessing fuel and time remaining to complete profile.\r\nStudent computes planned points to accomplish descent checks and desired descent point. Instructors should slew them from level off to this point to avoid long enroute drone time.\r\nPractice enroute descent and approach procedures\r\nStudent briefs to and practices turning off on the appropriate taxiway for desired parking location.\r\nSpecial Syllabus Requirements\r\nFly this mission under night conditions",
